==English==

===Etymology===
Ultimately from the {{etyl|la}} term {{term|aridus|āridus|dry, arid, parched|lang=la}}, confer its synonymous contracted form {{term|ardus|lang=la}}. Originally from the verb {{term|areo|āreo|I am dry, I am parched|lang=la}}, akin to {{term|ardeo|ārdeō|I'm on fire, I burn|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈæ.ɹɪd/}} {{SAMPA|/{.rId/}}
* {{audio|en-us-arid.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|arid|er|more}}
{{wikipedia}}

# Very [[dry]].
# Describing a very dry [[climate]].  Typically defined as less than 25 cm or 10 inches of rainfall annually.
# [[devoid|Devoid]] of [[value]].

